Package com.sri.ai.expresso.api

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CompoundSyntaxTree
    A SyntaxTree with children.
    CountingFormula
    An Expression that represents a counting formula, for example:
    ExistentiallyQuantifiedFormula
    An Expression that represents an existentially quantified formula.
    Expression
    An Expression is an algebraic expression based on a syntax tree.
    ExpressionAndSyntacticContext
    An ExpressionAndSyntacticContext encapsulates information about a sub-expression and the context in which it appears.
    ExtensionalSet
    An Expression that represents an extensionally defined set.
    FunctionApplication
    An Expression that represents a function application.
    IndexExpressionsSet
    Represents an immutable set of index expressions of an intensional set.
    IntensionalSet
    An Expression that represents an intensionally defined set.
    LambdaExpression
    An Expression that represents a lambda expression.
    Parser
    A parser maps strings to the corresponding Expressions.
    Parser.ErrorListener  
    QuantifiedExpression
    An Expression that represents a quantified expression, that is, an expression introducing new variables, such as universal and existential quantified expressions, intensional sets, and lambda expressions.
    QuantifiedExpressionWithABody
    An ExpressionStepSolver of the form IDENTIFIER : .
    ReplacementFunctionWithContextuallyUpdatedProcess
    A type of replacement function to be used by Expression's replace function.
    SubExpressionAddress
    A SubExpressionAddress represents the relative position of a sub-expression within its parent expression.
    Symbol
    An Expression that represents a symbol.
    SyntacticFunctionApplication
    An Expression that represents a syntactic function application (that is, something that takes expressions themselves, rather than their values, as arguments).
    SyntaxLeaf
    A SyntaxTree with no children.
    SyntaxTree
    A Syntax tree (also known as syntactic tree).
    Tuple
    An Expression that represents a tuple of sub-expressions.
    Type
    Represents the type of expressions.
    UniversallyQuantifiedFormula
    An Expression that represents a universally quantified formula.
